axis: cross-host-resume
status: pending-codec
needs: DurableValue wire codec + a second runner (JVM↔JS/Swift/Rust)
expected: A capsule saved on the portable-VM resumes on a DIFFERENT compatible
  host (Portable CodeMode + Durable FrameGate), producing byte-identical
  observable output. This is the axis the whole DurableValue/ExactArtifact model
  exists to enable; the portable-VM spike currently reports this ✗ (no capsule).
progress: The ExactArtifact half is now demonstrated cross-lane between the two
  qualified host runtimes (JVM + JS). A canonical "cross-host" capsule (id
  cross-host, timesTen machine, int frame, format v3) is FROZEN to byte-identical
  bytes by both host lanes AND decoded+restored+run by both (Scala
  CrossHostResumeTest, JS control.test.js), closing the JVM↔JS N→M cross product
  transitively. The Portable CodeMode half now also has a foundation: the reference
  VM has a `run-capsule` runner (`v2/src/Capsule.scala`, `ssc freeze-capsule` /
  `ssc run-capsule`) where the resume PROGRAM travels as closed CoreIR bytes and is
  admitted+run in a SEPARATE process holding no machine (digest-verified, fail-closed
  decode); demonstrated by `v2/conformance/portable-capsule.sh` (freeze in one JVM,
  run in another → frame*10+input; tamper rejected). The §10.2 GENERATION pass has
  its first slice too: `v2/src/SaveRegion.scala` (`ssc freeze-region`) closure-converts
  a compiler-declared saveable region (frame captures a,b; resume (a,b,input)=>a*input+b)
  into a GENERATED closed resume Program — a frame tuple + a `Lam(2,...)` that
  destructures it and applies the region lambda — run by the same machine-less runner
  (`portable-capsule.sh`: reified region → 19/10). NOT YET FLIPPED: the reification is
  first-order (explicit scalar slots); auto-liveness, global closure, effectful regions
  (`specs/portable-save-region.md` staging), and a SECOND admitting backend for the full
  §14.4 cross-backend N→M matrix remain.
sketch: |
  # capsule produced here, resumed by another runner profile's harness row.
